---
import ComponentDoc from '../../layouts/ComponentDoc.astro';
import Section from '@esa/docs/Section.astro';
import Preview from '@esa/docs/Preview.astro';
import Api from '@esa/docs/Api.astro';
import PropsTable from '@esa/docs/PropsTable.astro';
import Card from '@esa/ecology/esa-card.astro';

const props = [
  { name: 'title', type: 'string', description: 'Header title. Presence (or a header/actions slot) renders the header band.' },
  { name: 'subtitle', type: 'string', description: 'Secondary line under the title.' },
  { name: 'icon', type: 'string', description: 'Lucide icon name shown left of the title.' },
  { name: 'variant', type: "'default' | 'outlined' | 'elevated' | 'filled' | 'plain'", default: "'default'", description: 'Surface treatment: bordered (default/outlined), shadowed (elevated), sunken (filled), or none (plain — structure only, for cards inside an already-bounded region).' },
  { name: 'headerVariant', type: "'default' | 'primary' | 'muted'", default: "'default'", description: 'Header band tint.' },
  { name: 'headingLevel', type: '2 | 3 | 4 | 5 | 6', default: '3', description: 'Heading level of the title element. Match the card’s place in the document outline — a card directly under a page h1 should use 2 so the outline doesn’t skip a level (WCAG 1.3.1). Visual size is unchanged; only the tag differs.' },
  { name: 'padding', type: "'none' | 'compact' | 'default' | 'spacious'", default: "'default'", description: 'Body and header padding scale.' },
];

const slots = [
  { name: 'default', type: 'slot', description: 'Card body content.' },
  { name: 'header', type: 'slot', description: 'Replaces the title block entirely with custom markup.' },
  { name: 'actions', type: 'slot', description: 'Right-aligned controls in the header band.' },
  { name: 'footer', type: 'slot', description: 'Bottom band below the body.' },
];
---
<ComponentDoc name="Card" category="Display" slug="esa-card" type=".astro" status="stable"
  summary="Surface container with an optional header (icon, title, subtitle, actions), body, and footer. Variants, header tints, and padding scales.">

  <Section id="preview" title="Preview">
    <Preview align="start" code={`<Card title="Report" subtitle="Q3 summary">
  <p>Body content for the card.</p>
</Card>`}>
      <div style="width: 320px;">
        <Card title="Report" subtitle="Q3 summary">
          <p style="margin: 0;">Body content for the card.</p>
        </Card>
      </div>
    </Preview>
  </Section>

  <Section id="variants" title="Variants">
    <Preview align="start" code={`<Card title="Default" subtitle="Bordered surface">…</Card>
<Card variant="elevated" title="Elevated" subtitle="Shadow, no border">…</Card>
<Card variant="filled" title="Filled" subtitle="Sunken background">…</Card>`}>
      <div style="display: flex; gap: 16px; flex-wrap: wrap;">
        <div style="width: 240px;"><Card title="Default" subtitle="Bordered surface"><p style="margin: 0;">Default card.</p></Card></div>
        <div style="width: 240px;"><Card variant="elevated" title="Elevated" subtitle="Shadow, no border"><p style="margin: 0;">Elevated card.</p></Card></div>
        <div style="width: 240px;"><Card variant="filled" title="Filled" subtitle="Sunken background"><p style="margin: 0;">Filled card.</p></Card></div>
      </div>
    </Preview>
  </Section>

  <Section id="plain" title="Plain (structure only)">
    <p>The <code>plain</code> variant draws no box — no border, shadow, or fill. Use it when the card already sits inside a bounded region (a panel, a bordered list, another card) and a second container would just add visual noise. Below, three plain cards share one outer surface, separated by their own structure rather than individual borders.</p>
    <Preview align="start" code={`<Card variant="plain" title="Overview">…</Card>`}>
      <div style="width: 100%; max-width: 420px; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-300); background: var(--color-surface); padding: 8px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 4px;">
        <Card variant="plain" title="Overview" padding="compact"><p style="margin: 0;">No box of its own — it borrows the panel's edge.</p></Card>
        <Card variant="plain" title="Details" padding="compact"><p style="margin: 0;">Sits flush with its siblings.</p></Card>
        <Card variant="plain" title="History" padding="compact"><p style="margin: 0;">Structure without a second container.</p></Card>
      </div>
    </Preview>
  </Section>

  <Section id="header-variants" title="Header variants">
    <Preview align="start" code={`<Card headerVariant="primary" title="Primary header" subtitle="Inverted text">…</Card>
<Card headerVariant="muted" title="Muted header">…</Card>`}>
      <div style="display: flex; gap: 16px; flex-wrap: wrap;">
        <div style="width: 260px;"><Card headerVariant="primary" title="Primary header" subtitle="Inverted text"><p style="margin: 0;">Tinted header band.</p></Card></div>
        <div style="width: 260px;"><Card headerVariant="muted" title="Muted header"><p style="margin: 0;">Subtle sunken header.</p></Card></div>
      </div>
    </Preview>
  </Section>

  <Section id="padding" title="Padding">
    <Preview align="start" code={`<Card padding="compact" title="Compact">…</Card>
<Card padding="default" title="Default">…</Card>
<Card padding="spacious" title="Spacious">…</Card>`}>
      <div style="display: flex; gap: 16px; flex-wrap: wrap;">
        <div style="width: 200px;"><Card padding="compact" title="Compact"><p style="margin: 0;">Tighter body.</p></Card></div>
        <div style="width: 200px;"><Card padding="default" title="Default"><p style="margin: 0;">Standard body.</p></Card></div>
        <div style="width: 200px;"><Card padding="spacious" title="Spacious"><p style="margin: 0;">Roomy body.</p></Card></div>
      </div>
    </Preview>
  </Section>

  <Section id="slots" title="Actions & footer">
    <p>The <code>actions</code> slot sits at the right of the header; the <code>footer</code> slot renders a bottom band.</p>
    <Preview align="start" code={`<Card title="Report" subtitle="Q3 summary" icon="info">
  <button slot="actions" type="button">Edit</button>
  <p>Body content.</p>
  <span slot="footer">Last updated 2 hours ago</span>
</Card>`}>
      <div style="width: 420px; max-width: 100%;">
        <Card title="Report" subtitle="Q3 summary" icon="info">
          <button slot="actions" type="button">Edit</button>
          <p style="margin: 0;">The actions slot sits at the right of the header; the footer slot renders a bottom band.</p>
          <span slot="footer">Last updated 2 hours ago</span>
        </Card>
      </div>
    </Preview>
  </Section>

  <Section id="heading-level" title="Heading level (document outline)">
    <p>The title defaults to <code>&lt;h3&gt;</code>. When a card sits directly under a higher heading, set <code>headingLevel</code> so the outline stays contiguous — the <strong>visual size is identical</strong>, only the tag (and thus the a11y outline) changes.</p>
    <Preview align="start" code={`<!-- card directly under a page <h1> -->
<Card title="Section title" headingLevel={2}>…</Card>`}>
      <div style="width: 320px;">
        <Card title="Rendered as h2" subtitle="Same look, correct outline" headingLevel={2} data-demo-h="2">
          <p style="margin: 0;">Inspect the title — it's an <code>&lt;h2&gt;</code>.</p>
        </Card>
      </div>
    </Preview>
  </Section>

  <Section id="api" title="API">
    <Api props={props} />
    <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Slots</h3>
    <PropsTable rows={slots} />
  </Section>

  <Section id="accessibility" title="Accessibility">
    <ul class="a11y">
      <li>Renders a plain <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> — add <code>role</code>/landmarks at the call site if the card is interactive or a region.</li>
      <li>The title defaults to <code>&lt;h3&gt;</code>. Set <code>headingLevel</code> to keep the document outline contiguous — e.g. a card directly under a page <code>&lt;h1&gt;</code> should pass <code>headingLevel={'{2}'}</code> so it doesn't jump <code>h1&nbsp;→&nbsp;h3</code> (axe <em>heading-order</em> / WCAG 1.3.1).</li>
      <li>The header icon is <code>aria-hidden</code> — it decorates the title, not replaces it.</li>
    </ul>
  </Section>

</ComponentDoc>
